DPAH Analytics — Consolidated BRD v2.0

For: AI coding assistant (Chatbot 2 implementation)
Date: July 2026
Status: Final — approved for development Monday


PART 1 — SCOPE AND CONSTRAINTS
What We Are Building

A new Analytics capability inside the existing DPAH Chatbot 2 application. Users access it via a dedicated Analytics sidebar button. They select a module (RMS / HRMS / MRR), type a natural language question, and receive a chart, table, or text insight drawn from that module's operational database tables.

Hard Constraints
Work only on Chatbot 2. Do not touch Chatbot 1.
Do not modify existing workflow graphs (RMS, HRMS, MRR). They are untouched.
Do not introduce new database roles. Reuse JUNIOR/MID/SENIOR with existing RBAC.
Do not expose RBAC system tables to the LLM under any circumstances.
All SQL generated by LLM must be SELECT only and validated before execution.
Phase 1: SQL_DATA and SQL_INSIGHT routing only. RAG returns "not available" message.
One analytics LangGraph — not one per module. Module context is passed as a parameter.

What Is Out of Scope (Phase 1)
RAG-based analytics answers
Hybrid SQL + RAG answers
Cross-module queries (cannot join RMS and MRR tables in one query)
Write operations of any kind
Scheduled reports or exports
Chatbot 1 changes

